<TITLE> DSE posts steady surge </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 26 (bdnews24.com) - Dhaka stocks rallied in midday trade Tuesday, paced by a steady surge in the banking, power and cement shares. The market fell slightly amid sell-offs after a vertical ride in the opening. It regained pace in the midday session as investors resumed buying. The DGEN or general index rallied 16.92 points or 0.79 percent to reach 2145.85 at 12.47pm. The DSI or all-share price index climbed 23.90 points or 1.37 percent to 1768.11. Of the issues traded, 102 gained, 70 fell and 20 held steady. Turnover reached Tk 1.40 billion in midday trade. Total turnover was Tk 1.70 billion at Monday's close. DESCO, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh, Heidelberg Cement, BRAC Bank and Southeast Bank topped the turnover board at 12.35pm. DESCO dropped to Tk 937 from Monday's Tk 954.25. Power Grid fell to Tk 586.5 from Tk 596.35 as investor locked in gains. Heidelberg Cement rose to Tk 1,100 from Tk 1,064.75. BRAC Bank dropped to Tk 761 from Tk 771.75. Southeast Bank grew to Tk 491.5 from Tk 480.25. Of the remaining five issues in turnover, Pubali Bank, National Bank, EXIM Bank, Rupali Bank traded upbeat. Square Pharma held steady. 
